<taxonomicName authority="(sensu Weir et al. 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Weir" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[279,693,1955,1981]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Melolonthini">
Melolonthini (
<emphasis box="[440,502,1956,1981]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Weir, T. A. &amp; Lawrence, J. F. &amp; Lemann, C. &amp; Gunter, N. L." box="[508,685,1955,1981]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" pagination="467 - 507" refId="ref2937" refString="Weir, T. A., Lawrence, J. F., Lemann, C. &amp; Gunter, N. L. (2019) Scarabaeidae: Melolonthinae Leach, 1819. In: Slipinski, A. &amp; Lawrence, J. F. (Eds.), Australian Beetles. Vol. 2. Archostemata, Myxophaga, Adephaga, Polyphaga (part). CSIRO Publishing, Clayton, pp. 467 - 507." type="book chapter" year="2019">
Weir 
<emphasis box="[567,622,1955,1981]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
with: head, pronotum and elytra black, contrasting with brown elytra (
<figureCitation box="[195,271,1991,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1978,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Hypolepida wilsoni Britton, 1978. 1, Dorsum of male; 2, section of pronotum, scutellum and elytra; 3, antennal club of male; 4, parameres, dorsal view; 5, parameres, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677949/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[284,300,1991,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1650,1675]" captionTargetBox="[241,1374,400,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[185,1374,378,1606]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Hypolepida braes Allsopp, new species, holotype. 7, Dorsum of male; 8, antennal club of male; 9, parameres, dorsal view; 10, parameres, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677953/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">7</figureCitation>
); antennae with 10 antennomeres with a 6-lamellate or 7-lamellate club in male (
<figureCitation box="[1194,1271,1991,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1978,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Hypolepida wilsoni Britton, 1978. 1, Dorsum of male; 2, section of pronotum, scutellum and elytra; 3, antennal club of male; 4, parameres, dorsal view; 5, parameres, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677949/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1283,1298,1991,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1650,1675]" captionTargetBox="[241,1374,400,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[185,1374,378,1606]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Hypolepida braes Allsopp, new species, holotype. 7, Dorsum of male; 8, antennal club of male; 9, parameres, dorsal view; 10, parameres, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677953/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">8</figureCitation>
); profemora and protibiae, head, pronotum, scutellum and elytra with elongate, flattened, adpressed setae (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1264,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1978,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Hypolepida wilsoni Britton, 1978. 1, Dorsum of male; 2, section of pronotum, scutellum and elytra; 3, antennal club of male; 4, parameres, dorsal view; 5, parameres, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), head and disc of pronotum without long setae, pronotal hypopleura with long setae, without circular white scales contained within their punctures on either dorsal or ventral surfaces; terminal palpomere of maxillary palp with an obvious dorsal flat area; anterior face of clypeus with ratio of greatest width to mid length 4–6:1; upper surface of clypeus not deeply concave but with slightly reflexed anterior margin, outline broadly rounded; junctions between abdominal ventrites 1–5 much less obvious in the middle than on the sides; anterior edge of metafemora not concave near base; both spurs of metatibia slender, upper one slightly longer than lower; claws with a tooth on the concave side; male parameres bilaterally symmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[499,607,404,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1978,2003]" captionTargetBox="[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[177,1410,306,1950]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Hypolepida wilsoni Britton, 1978. 1, Dorsum of male; 2, section of pronotum, scutellum and elytra; 3, antennal club of male; 4, parameres, dorsal view; 5, parameres, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677949/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">Figs. 4–5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[619,679,405,431]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1650,1675]" captionTargetBox="[241,1374,400,1606]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[185,1374,378,1606]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. Hypolepida braes Allsopp, new species, holotype. 7, Dorsum of male; 8, antennal club of male; 9, parameres, dorsal view; 10, parameres, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677953" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677953/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="596">9–10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
